## B. Violation and Payment Recording Workflow

1. The traffic enforcer issues a paper ticket to the traffic violator.

2. The traffic violator proceeds to the TMO or Treasury Office to settle or record the violation.

3. The treasury personnel opens the TRAVIS mobile application or web application.

4. The treasury personnel logs in using an authorized account.

5. The treasury personnel selects whether to use Manual Input or Scan Input.

6. If Manual Input is selected, the treasury personnel manually encodes the ticket details.

7. If Scan Input is selected, the treasury personnel scans the paper ticket using OCR.

8. The OCR module extracts ticket details such as ticket number, driver name, license number, plate number, vehicle type, violation type, violation location, violation date, violation time, and penalty amount.

9. The treasury personnel reviews and verifies the extracted or manually encoded ticket details.

10. The treasury personnel records the payment information and payment status.

11. The violation and payment details are saved in the centralized database.

12. The system updates the violation records, payment records, and dashboard reports.

13. The administrator or authorized personnel can view violation records, payment status, and payment reports through the web dashboard.

14. End of Violation and Payment Recording Workflow.

